ed in the near\npast. As an alternative scenario, single-star evolution through late core\nhelium flash and atmospheric mixing can also produce the observed fluorine\nabundances. The atmospheric metal over-abundances currently observed are\nperhaps the results of a combination of mixing processes during formation and\nradiative support.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 7 Jul 2021 15:03:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-01"}
